- Gabriel, don't do this.
- Give me the box.

764
01:09:59,899 --> 01:10:02,896
What, you want more money? Hell...
look around you. Take what you want.

765
01:10:02,898 --> 01:10:06,131
Just, shut up
and give me the box.

766
01:10:06,737 --> 01:10:09,235
What about Alex?
Nicky will kill her. You know that.

767
01:10:09,237 --> 01:10:11,774
I will ask you one more time.

768
01:10:13,055 --> 01:10:15,795
Why are you doing this?

769
01:10:15,796 --> 01:10:21,213
I'm a cop...
In Miami for the last ten years.

770
01:10:21,215 --> 01:10:23,893
Weber requested me.
Just for you.

771
01:10:27,453 --> 01:10:30,851
So you're a cop.
You wanna arrest me? Go ahead.

772
01:10:30,853 --> 01:10:32,652
Where am I gonna go?

773
01:10:32,653 --> 01:10:36,451
But in one minute that vault door's
gonna lock and we'll be stuck in here...

774
01:10:36,452 --> 01:10:38,411
and Alex is gonna be dead.

775
01:10:38,412 --> 01:10:41,090
I can't believe you're such
a contemptible human being...

776
01:10:41,091 --> 01:10:43,729
that you would use her like that
and then just kill her...

777
01:10:43,730 --> 01:10:46,168
cos you might as well
be pulling the trigger yourself.

778
01:10:46,170 --> 01:10:49,609
Simply to bag
the great Keith Ripley.

779
01:10:50,210 --> 01:10:53,443
You sorry, sick motherfucker.

780
01:10:56,257 --> 01:10:59,636
- You got 30 seconds.
- How do I find Nicky?

781
01:11:00,368 --> 01:11:02,166
Phone number in my pocket.

782
01:11:02,167 --> 01:11:04,877
Give it to me...
and the eggs.

783
01:11:05,487 --> 01:11:09,079
- Do you want her alive or not?
- Do you?

784
01:11:21,524 --> 01:11:23,313
Ten seconds.

785
01:11:24,762 --> 01:11:26,551
I'm sorry.

786
01:11:54,158 --> 01:11:55,396
Underground, boys.

787
01:11:55,398 --> 01:11:58,073
All right, let's move!
Come on!

788
01:12:43,548 --> 01:12:46,467
I'm a police officer!
Listen to me.

789
01:12:46,469 --> 01:12:48,426
There is a thief
locked in your inner vault.

790
01:12:48,427 --> 01:12:50,707
The guard is in the basement closet.

791
01:12:50,707 --> 01:12:54,786
Move, move, move,
move, move!

792
01:12:54,787 --> 01:12:57,265
Now! Move! Come on!

793
01:12:57,266 --> 01:13:00,181
Tell them to put
their weapons down now.

794
01:13:01,305 --> 01:13:03,104
Now!

795
01:13:03,105 --> 01:13:05,702
Okay. Fine.

796
01:13:07,824 --> 01:13:09,144
Put them down:

797
01:13:09,145 --> 01:13:10,342
Now!

798
01:13:15,423 --> 01:13:18,100
Kick them. Now!

799
01:13:20,422 --> 01:13:22,301
What do you want?

800
01:13:22,301 --> 01:13:25,461
You let me out the front door
so I can rejoin my unit.

801
01:13:25,462 --> 01:13:27,460
They have the building surrounded.

802
01:13:27,461 --> 01:13:30,979
Meantime, you go downstairs,
you find your thief and your comrade.

803
01:13:30,980 --> 01:13:33,578
- You understand?
- That door is alarmed.

804
01:13:33,579 --> 01:13:35,139
You have a problem, solve it.

805
01:13:35,140 --> 01:13:38,213
Do not make me
shoot this man, please.

806
01:14:15,012 --> 01:14:17,331
- Put down your weapons.
- We are police!

807
01:14:17,332 --> 01:14:20,610
Yeah? Everybody's police tonight.

808
01:14:27,091 --> 01:14:28,128
Hello?

809
01:14:28,130 --> 01:14:31,887
Hey, I have what you want.
No, it's just me.

810
01:14:52,126 --> 01:14:56,600
Can we talk?
I have a proposition for you.

811
01:15:06,604 --> 01:15:08,391
Where is she?

812
01:15:12,323 --> 01:15:16,720
Do not move.
He has a gun behind the box.

813
01:15:16,721 --> 01:15:17,841
Bad boy.

814
01:15:17,841 --> 01:15:20,960
Give me the box
and give Andrei your weapon, please.

815
01:15:20,961 --> 01:15:22,239
We don't wish trouble here.

816
01:15:22,240 --> 01:15:24,238
No, no, no.
You don't understand.

817
01:15:24,239 --> 01:15:26,759
You let her go,
then I'll give you the box.

818
01:15:26,760 --> 01:15:30,557
You see, if I fire through this box,

819
01:15:30,559 --> 01:15:32,997
which I have no problem
doing what so ever,

820
01:15:32,998 --> 01:15:34,677
Nicky's not gonna
be very happy.

821
01:15:34,679 --> 01:15:37,115
Then we are all expendable.

822
01:15:37,637 --> 01:15:39,676
If you understand
the meaning of the word.

823
01:15:39,677 --> 01:15:41,796
Open the box.

824
01:15:42,497 --> 01:15:44,756
Lower the gun.
Lower the gun.

825
01:15:44,756 --> 01:15:47,466
Lower it.

826
01:15:51,475 --> 01:15:53,310
Okay.

827
01:16:00,194 --> 01:16:03,551
- Are you all right?
- Yeah. I'm just lovely. Thanks.

828
01:16:03,552 --> 01:16:06,582
You go.

829
01:16:13,591 --> 01:16:15,426
Give me the box.

830
01:16:18,150 --> 01:16:20,029
- Get in.
- Why?

831
01:16:20,029 --> 01:16:22,342
Nicky wants too see you.

832
01:16:23,869 --> 01:16:25,863
Give me your weapon.

833
01:16:26,548 --> 01:16:28,828
We're fine, right?

834
01:16:36,987 --> 01:16:39,746
Where do you get off detaining us?

835
01:16:39,747 --> 01:16:41,506
My apologies, Lieutenant Weber.

836
01:16:41,506 --> 01:16:44,225
My security were,
understandably, confused.

837
01:16:44,225 --> 01:16:46,904
Please go with Mr. Sergev
down to the vault.

838
01:16:46,905 --> 01:16:49,774
We have what you want. Please.

839
01:16:58,583 --> 01:17:02,502
- Where's the other one?
- Nobody else. Just him.

840
01:17:02,502 --> 01:17:04,974
Where the hell's my man?

841
01:17:05,462 --> 01:17:11,176
Lieutenant, your personal life,
none of my business.

842
01:17:11,780 --> 01:17:15,333
I apologize for bringing you here...

843
01:17:15,699 --> 01:17:20,019
but I had to be sure the eggs
were genuine before I let you go.

844
01:17:20,020 --> 01:17:25,051
Your lack of trust
is really depressing, Mr. Petrovich.

845
01:17:26,099 --> 01:17:28,774
I'm a man of my word.

846
01:17:29,858 --> 01:17:32,851
She should be with her godfather now.

847
01:17:35,016 --> 01:17:37,011
Let's see.

848
01:17:37,497 --> 01:17:40,092
- Do you mind?
- Sure... Call.

849
01:17:47,135 --> 01:17:48,923
Yeah.

850
01:17:53,094 --> 01:17:56,453
- Hello?
- Hey. Where are you?

851
01:17:56,972 --> 01:17:59,572
I'm at the jail. I had to see him.

852
01:17:59,573 --> 01:18:00,890
How is he?

853
01:18:00,891 --> 01:18:02,490
Well, how do you think he is?

854
01:18:02,492 --> 01:18:05,131
I had no choice, Alex.

855
01:18:05,131 --> 01:18:06,409
No one had a choice.

856
01:18:06,411 --> 01:18:11,488
Remember? I told you.
Neither one of us could promise a thing.

857
01:18:11,489 --> 01:18:14,929
Listen, promises blow away in the wind.

858
01:18:14,930 --> 01:18:16,807
But feelings are real.

859
01:18:16,809 --> 01:18:20,368
And I need to know
were the feelings lies, too?

860
01:18:20,368 --> 01:18:23,921
Listen, listen.
What I mean is...

861
01:18:24,408 --> 01:18:26,402
are we real?

862
01:18:31,287 --> 01:18:36,005
- I've gotta go, Gabriel. Good night.
- Walt Don't go

863
01:18:36,006 --> 01:18:38,284
Hold...

864
01:18:45,724 --> 01:18:48,115
Are you satisfied?

865
01:18:55,881 --> 01:18:58,400
Did you see them?

866
01:18:58,402 --> 01:19:02,238
- Actually, we were in a hurry.
- Look.

867
01:19:11,560 --> 01:19:13,757
They are simply...

868
01:19:13,759 --> 01:19:15,673
wood?

869
01:19:33,395 --> 01:19:36,583
- Oh, my God:
- Simply wood?

870
01:19:39,914 --> 01:19:42,313
It was 1917, Gabriel.

871
01:19:42,314 --> 01:19:44,953
Russia. People were starving.

872
01:19:44,953 --> 01:19:48,712
There were no jewels,
no diamonds left.

873
01:19:48,712 --> 01:19:50,945
No hope.

874
01:19:51,193 --> 01:19:55,427
Yet Czarina Alexandra
had to have her eggs.

875
01:19:56,671 --> 01:20:00,144
Perhaps you understand
why we had a revolution.

876
01:20:01,150 --> 01:20:04,225
People needed
to believe in something.

877
01:20:06,590 --> 01:20:09,106
Take him home.

878
01:20:14,068 --> 01:20:15,983
Gabriel.

879
01:20:18,948 --> 01:20:23,296
I know what they say about me
but I'm not a killer.

880
01:20:23,627 --> 01:20:27,024
Merely a humble immigrant.

881
01:20:27,025 --> 01:20:29,463
Probably much like you.

882
01:20:30,345 --> 01:20:32,975
I don't think so, Mr. Petrovich.

883
01:20:34,104 --> 01:20:36,974
You're not like me at all.

884
01:20:47,381 --> 01:20:50,661
Excellent. Thanks.
We've got Petrovich.

885
01:20:50,662 --> 01:20:54,340
Snitch called it in. After all this time
looking for him, you know where he was?

886
01:20:54,341 --> 01:20:56,579
I'm sure you'll tell us.

887
01:20:56,581 --> 01:20:58,498
On the boardwalk,
watchin ' the sun come up.

888
01:20:58,500 --> 01:21:02,609
He's coming in now.
I'll be right back.

889
01:21:04,219 --> 01:21:08,578
Yeah, what I didn't count on
was that a so-called professional...

890
01:21:08,578 --> 01:21:10,577
would be manipulated by a chick.

891
01:21:10,578 --> 01:21:12,337
What kind of cops
do they make in Miami?

892
01:21:12,337 --> 01:21:14,537
Good ones, Weber.
Good ones.

893
01:21:14,537 --> 01:21:16,416
I don't get it.

894
01:21:16,417 --> 01:21:20,493
All these years in that world.
How do you let an asset use you?

895
01:21:21,256 --> 01:21:23,734
Sometimes things... change.

896
01:21:23,735 --> 01:21:27,854
Things change?
Like, "which side am I on" change?

897
01:21:27,854 --> 01:21:30,333
Ripley, what is he,
your best friend now?

898
01:21:30,335 --> 01:21:32,292
Actually, a better friend than you.

899
01:21:32,293 --> 01:21:35,172
Ah, I get it. I'm the asshole.

900
01:21:35,173 --> 01:21:37,212
You're gonna tell me
what a good guy he is...

901
01:21:37,213 --> 01:21:40,011
or how he got caught up
in a situation he couldn't control,

902
01:21:40,012 --> 01:21:42,612
or how the sins of the father
shouldn't rest on the daughter?

903
01:21:42,613 --> 01:21:45,610
Give me something better
than, "things change".

904
01:21:45,612 --> 01:21:49,561
All I can give you is the truth.

905
01:21:50,530 --> 01:21:54,800
Oh, fuck it.
Go back to Miami, Martin.

906
01:21:56,529 --> 01:22:00,448
When your superiors get my report,
you'll be lucky if you have a job.

907
01:22:00,448 --> 01:22:02,328
We'll see.

908
01:22:02,328 --> 01:22:04,207
Hey, say anything
you want about Ripley...

909
01:22:04,208 --> 01:22:06,646
but nothing changes
the fact that I finally got him.

910
01:22:06,648 --> 01:22:11,282
Now when he leaves prison,
he'll be leaving in a pine box.

911
01:22:11,886 --> 01:22:14,086
Let's go see Mr. Petrovich.

912
01:22:26,925 --> 01:22:28,759
No.

913
01:22:34,483 --> 01:22:37,921
- That's not Nicky Petrovich.
- What?

914
01:22:38,443 --> 01:22:40,230
Not him.

915
01:22:42,681 --> 01:22:46,079
Look, man, Organized Crime
confirmed it. That's Nicky Petrovich.

916
01:22:46,081 --> 01:22:48,800
Well, I don't care. That's not him.

917
01:22:48,801 --> 01:22:51,719
I was there, remember?

918
01:22:51,720 --> 01:22:53,838
There's no case here.

919
01:22:53,840 --> 01:22:57,518
- What? Of course there's a case.
- You really think I'll put him on the stand?

920
01:22:57,519 --> 01:23:00,837
An undercover Miami cop
who may or may not be legit?

921
01:23:00,838 --> 01:23:01,957
- No offence.
- None taken.

922
01:23:01,957 --> 01:23:04,997
A cop who's the centerpiece
of a botched undercover operation...

923
01:23:04,997 --> 01:23:07,115
that was officially ordered stopped?

924
01:23:07,117 --> 01:23:09,796
I won't embarrass the Bureau,
much less your department,

925
01:23:09,796 --> 01:23:13,034
which accepted tons of money
and equipment from the Russian Mafia.

926
01:23:13,036 --> 01:23:16,755
What about Romanov's? What about
the goddamn stolen treasures of Russia?

927
01:23:16,756 --> 01:23:17,875
What about it, Weber?

928
01:23:17,876 --> 01:23:19,514
When Zykov found Ripley in the vault,

929
01:23:19,515 --> 01:23:21,873
he had everything cleared out
before you could get in.

930
01:23:21,875 --> 01:23:24,432
I have a proposition for you.

931
01:23:24,434 --> 01:23:27,712
There's no way Romanov's
will press charges against Ripley.

932
01:23:27,713 --> 01:23:32,152
Cos they can never admit that the eggs
or anything else ever existed.

933
01:23:32,153 --> 01:23:34,990
So we can't even prove
that Detective Martin and Ripley.

934
01:23:34,992 --> 01:23:36,310
stole even a goddamn dime.

935
01:23:36,311 --> 01:23:38,625
But you must have mug shots.

936
01:23:38,671 --> 01:23:41,701
Russian Mafia,
known associates, something.

937
01:24:04,106 --> 01:24:06,260
That's him.

938
01:24:06,827 --> 01:24:08,585
That's Nicky Petrovich.

939
01:24:08,586 --> 01:24:11,694
- Detective Martin...
- Yeah?

940
01:24:12,105 --> 01:24:14,657
That's Victor Korolenko.

941
01:24:24,543 --> 01:24:26,492
Presumed dead.

942
01:24:26,783 --> 01:24:29,698
We just never found the body.

943
01:24:33,221 --> 01:24:35,659
You never will...

944
01:24:36,060 --> 01:24:37,975
Lieutenant.

945
01:25:21,092 --> 01:25:22,851
Weber.

946
01:25:22,853 --> 01:25:23,891
What?

947
01:25:23,893 --> 01:25:27,251
His lawyer got him in front of a judge
on an expedited bail hearing.

948
01:25:27,252 --> 01:25:28,770
Then he just walked.

949
01:25:28,771 --> 01:25:31,171
- Who was it?
- Who was what?

950
01:25:31,171 --> 01:25:34,770
- The lawyer.
- Who the fuck do you think?

951
01:25:34,770 --> 01:25:38,037
Alex. Korolenko.

952
01:25:59,287 --> 01:26:02,604
You can't promise me anything so...

953
01:26:02,605 --> 01:26:05,680
maybe we shouldn't even try.

954
01:26:43,998 --> 01:26:46,993
Papa.

955
01:26:47,518 --> 01:26:49,556
Shall we go?

956
01:27:00,475 --> 01:27:01,514
Yeah?

957
01:27:01,515 --> 01:27:04,434
Didn't wanna leave
without saying goodbye...

958
01:27:04,435 --> 01:27:06,953
I owe you one Gaby.

959
01:27:06,953 --> 01:27:08,313
The real Nicky Petrovich...

960
01:27:08,314 --> 01:27:11,992
is the one Zykov is funneling
the contraband through.

961
01:27:12,592 --> 01:27:16,511
Thank you, but Zykov and Petrovich
have gone to ground.

962
01:27:16,512 --> 01:27:19,110
- Check out a disco called...
- Riga Rose?

963
01:27:19,112 --> 01:27:22,030
Ahh, I see you're familiar
with the territory.

964
01:27:22,032 --> 01:27:24,829
Well... I am a cop, remember?

965
01:27:24,831 --> 01:27:26,670
I never forgot it for a second.

966
01:27:26,671 --> 01:27:28,550
When did you know?

967
01:27:28,551 --> 01:27:32,149
I knew you were coming
up from Miami before you did Gaby.

968
01:27:32,149 --> 01:27:33,429
See Weber and I...

969
01:27:33,430 --> 01:27:36,028
Well, let's just say
we share the same sources,

970
01:27:36,029 --> 01:27:37,507
only I pay better.

971
01:27:37,509 --> 01:27:39,028
Sir, we're good to go.

972
01:27:39,029 --> 01:27:41,546
So why the help Ripley?

973
01:27:41,547 --> 01:27:43,506
Maybe feeling guilty?

974
01:27:45,068 --> 01:27:47,466
Guilt's not even in my vocabulary.

975
01:27:47,466 --> 01:27:50,542
I was just hoping
you'd see things differently.

976
01:27:51,826 --> 01:27:54,935
Together you and I could do anything.

977
01:27:55,586 --> 01:27:58,663
Yeah. I believe we did.

978
01:27:58,664 --> 01:28:01,823
I'll get in touch later on,
if you're interested.

979
01:28:01,824 --> 01:28:03,962
Meanwhile, I've got to keep
an appointment with a man...

980
01:28:03,963 --> 01:28:05,903
who's gonna pay
dearly for something...

981
01:28:05,904 --> 01:28:09,854
he's got to keep locked
in his basement just to say it's his.

982
01:28:11,262 --> 01:28:13,939
- Good hunting, Gaby.
- Wait, wait, wait!

983
01:28:14,301 --> 01:28:16,180
Let me talk to her.
Just for a second.

984
01:28:16,181 --> 01:28:18,940
- That's him?
- What makes you think she's going anywhere?

985
01:28:18,942 --> 01:28:20,380
She didn't commit any crime.

986
01:28:20,381 --> 01:28:24,412
She just lied to someone
who was lying to her.

987
01:28:34,538 --> 01:28:36,537
You be good.

988
01:28:36,537 --> 01:28:39,293
I'll try, Uncle Keith.

989
01:28:39,537 --> 01:28:43,695
Although I suspect
my legal career just ended.

990
01:28:43,697 --> 01:28:46,692
Thank God.

991
01:29:14,851 --> 01:29:18,569
You come in here every night
and every night I tell you...

992
01:29:18,570 --> 01:29:21,929
I don't know shit
from this Petrovich.

993
01:29:23,329 --> 01:29:25,649
This is a nightclub, my friend.

994
01:29:25,649 --> 01:29:27,768
You know what I think?

995
01:29:28,168 --> 01:29:32,327
I think you need to check out
the action and get your ass laid.

996
01:29:32,328 --> 01:29:35,287
- Yeah.
- You know what I'm sayin', dude?

997
01:29:35,287 --> 01:29:38,157
Find yourself a chick.

998
01:29:48,286 --> 01:29:51,962
Vodka.

999
01:29:52,444 --> 01:29:53,804
Zakuska?

1000
01:29:53,805 --> 01:29:55,882
Russian hors d'eurvres
to coat the stomach.

1001
01:29:55,884 --> 01:29:57,912
Oh.

1002
01:29:58,163 --> 01:30:01,801
- Will my stomach need coating?
- I hope so.

1003
01:30:01,802 --> 01:30:04,162
I thought you didn't drink.

1004
01:30:04,162 --> 01:30:05,560
You thought a lot of things,

1005
01:30:05,561 --> 01:30:09,041
but I believe I mentioned something
about making assumptions.

1006
01:30:09,042 --> 01:30:12,920
Maybe that's a concept
we should get rid of. Immediately.

1007
01:30:12,921 --> 01:30:15,676
My name is Gabriel Martin.

1008
01:30:15,881 --> 01:30:17,908
I'm from Miami.

1009
01:30:18,279 --> 01:30:23,037
I was actually looking for a lawyer
but the office was closed.

1010
01:30:23,038 --> 01:30:24,757
So...

1011
01:30:24,759 --> 01:30:27,197
I came here.

1012
01:30:30,358 --> 01:30:32,237
Okay.

1013
01:30:32,238 --> 01:30:36,355
My name is Alexandra Korolenko...

1014
01:30:36,356 --> 01:30:39,675
